  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implementing Inclusive Education for Blind Children in Bombali Sierra (Sierra Leone)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Sierra Leone very few blind or visually impaired children go to school. Parents often don&#x2019;t see the benefit in them going, schools do not have the facilities or equipment required to teach them, and teachers aren&#x2019;t trained how to teach children with disabilities. This project focuses on helping blind children to go to school. It will support blind children and their families, provide practical training for teachers and support for the schools they teach in, as well as educating communities about the rights of blind children. It will help many children who have been denied an education to go to school and get an education, and provide a blueprint for this to happen across the whole country.</narrative>
  </description>
